According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Fidget Toys market was valued at USD 1.5 billion in 2024 and is projected to grow from USD 1.65 billion in 2025 to USD 3.2 billion by 2034, registering a CAGR of 7.8% during the forecast period. The market is expanding due to growing awareness of mental health, increasing adoption of stress-relief products, and rising demand for sensory tools among individuals with ADHD and autism spectrum disorders. Educational institutions, workplaces, and healthcare professionals are increasingly incorporating fidget toys to improve focus, reduce anxiety, and enhance productivity. Continuous product innovation, including ergonomic and silent designs for professional users, is further supporting market growth.
